This article is a letter from former President Barack Obama to the Speaker of the House of Representatives and the President of the Senate. In the letter, Obama states that he has sent a notice to the Federal Register to continue the national emergency declared with respect to foreign terrorists who threaten to disrupt the Middle East peace process. He explains that the crisis with respect to acts of violence committed by these terrorists has not been resolved, and their actions continue to pose a threat to the national security, foreign policy, and economy of the United States. Therefore, he has determined that it is necessary to maintain the national emergency and the economic sanctions against these terrorists.